We are looking for a Chat Service Solution to integrate within the Micro-service Architecture. The solution needs to ensure high throughput, withstand high workload, and have scalability. The testing of the service has to be conducted in a simple manner with Unit Testing, and can be integrated within the existing microservice of our web project.

More precisely:

In the first stage of development, we aim to create a chat service with core functionalities. Afterwards, there must be a possibility to develop the chat service by building new functionalities which will be synchronized with the previously established core functionalities.

Chat Service has to be developed in 2 stages:

1. First Stage - Chat with core functionalities;
2. Second Stage - Additional functionalities will be built on top of the existing core functionalities manufactured in the First Stage of the development.

1. First Stage - Core Functional:

Chat can be initiated between two users or between admin/moderator and a user;
Communication Type - Written Text;
Communication Status - “Sent”, “Seen”;
Database - In order to store communication between Interlocutors ;
Separate channel for the admin to communicate with the user/users;
When initiating a chat between the users, if there is a communication history between the mentioned users, the last block of the communication (block being a compilation of, for instance, 20 messages) has to be transferred from the database, and presented in the user communication interface;
Ability to present previous communication in the chat interface between users. For example: If “User A” aims to view previous communication he/she had with “User B”, the application must have a path to request the previous blocks of communication that exists between these two users from the Chat Service.

2. Second Stage - Additional Functionalities:

Communication types:

Voice/Audio communication;
Stickers;
Send Image;
GIF (from a library);
Short Video (Boomerang).

Automatically present a thumbnail whenever a link is sent;

Communication Status:

“Sent”, but the user is offline;
“Sent”, the user received, but has not viewed the communication content;
“Sent”, the user received the communication and viewed it.

Automated translation of the written communication - the text message sent by us to the user shall be automatically displayed in the user’s chosen/native language;

Ability to chat/conversate with Support:
Direct Chat;
Chatbot

